                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">
                        The Mona Lisa, painted by Leonardo da Vinci between 1503 and 1506, is one of the most iconic works of art in history. Displayed in the Louvre Museum in Paris, it features a woman with a mysterious smile, which has intrigued viewers for centuries. The use of sfumato, a technique of blending colors, adds to the painting's realism and lifelike presence. It represents the peak of Renaissance portraiture.
