                <div class="detailed-view-card-text-container">
                    <h1 class="detailed-view-card-heading">The Last Supper</h1>
                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">
                        Painted by Leonardo da Vinci between 1495 and 1498, The Last Supper captures the moment when Jesus announces that one of his disciples will betray him. It is located in the Convent of Santa Maria delle Grazie in Milan, Italy. This masterpiece is renowned for its innovative composition, dramatic use of perspective, and detailed portrayal of human emotion, representing a pivotal moment in Christian history.
                    </p>
