                    <h1 class="detailed-view-card-heading">Annunciation</h1>
                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">
                        Annunciation is an early work by Leonardo, created around 1472. It depicts the Angel Gabriel announcing to the Virgin Mary that she will conceive the Son of God. It was one of Leonardo's first masterpieces, demonstrating his skill in perspective and naturalistic portrayal of human figures. The work is held in the Uffizi Gallery in Florence, Italy.
